//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_graft}

NOTE: This operation grafts a locally-built container image into
{rbtgi_repository}
via native docker/podman push.
No Cloud Build involvement in the image push — the image is already built on the local workstation.
No crane dependency — docker tag + docker push is sufficient for locally-present images.
No dirty-tree guard — git state is irrelevant to an already-built container.

NOTE: The name "graft" comes from botanical grafting — foreign material spliced onto rootstock.
The graft may take or may not.
The metaphor fits the trust posture: grafted images have no provenance chain and receive a GRAFTED verdict from
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}.

NOTE: Graft uses whatever container runtime the `docker` command resolves to in PATH, matching other {rbtr_director}-side operations.
No separate regime variable governs runtime selection for graft.

NOTE: *Universal reliquary precondition*. Every ordain-path vessel — conjure, bind, and graft — must have `RBRV_RELIQUARY` non-empty before this operation runs. Graft's about+vouch combined Cloud Build job consumes reliquary tool images (gcloud, docker, alpine, syft) just like conjure and bind; the registry preflight enforces this before submission.

The
{rbtr_director}
grafts an image:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
local image reference provided as second argument (or defaulted from {rbrv_graft_image})
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel mode is {rbrv_vessel_mode_graft}

//axhos_step
. *Load Vessel Configuration*:
.. Source vessel configuration from the {rbrv_regime}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_SIGIL»` from {rbrv_sigil}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_MODE»` from {rbrv_vessel_mode}
.. {rbbc_require}
`«VESSEL_MODE»` is `rbnve_graft`

//axhos_step
. *Verify Local Image Exists*:
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker image inspect «LOCAL_IMAGE_REF»` (or podman equivalent)
.. {rbbc_require}
image exists in local container runtime
.. {rbbc_store}
`«LOCAL_DIGEST»` from local image inspect
.. {rbbc_store}
`«LOCAL_PLATFORMS»` from local image manifest (typically single-platform for local builds)

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Hallmark*:
.. {rbbc_call}
query local container runtime for image creation timestamp via `docker image inspect` (the `Created` field — OCI Image Configuration spec, exposed at `.Created` by both docker and podman)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«IMAGE_CREATED»` as the image's creation timestamp, converted to `YYMMDDHHMMSS` format
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PUSH_TIMESTAMP»` as current UTC time (`YYMMDDHHMMSS`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARK»` as `g«IMAGE_CREATED»-r«PUSH_TIMESTAMP»`
.. T1 encodes when the image was created (a fact about the artifact); T2 encodes when it was pushed to GAR
.. NOTE: The `created` field may be `1970-01-01T00:00:00Z` for reproducible builds. This produces `g700101000000-r...` — a true statement about the image, not an error.

//axhos_step
. *Tag and Push Image*:
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker login` to GAR registry with director credentials
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_TAG»` as `«GAR_HOST»/«GAR_PATH»/{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/image:«HALLMARK»`
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker tag «LOCAL_IMAGE_REF» «REGISTRY_TAG»`
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker push «REGISTRY_TAG»`
.. {rbbc_require}
push succeeds

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark_image}

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_hallmark}
The full
{rbtga_hallmark}
string.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_build_id}
Empty for graft — no
{gcb_build}
involvement in image push.
Written for uniform fact coverage.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_gar_root}
{gar_service}
registry prefix.
Composable with
{rbf_fact_ark_stem}
for full artifact references.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_ark_stem}
The hallmark subtree prefix `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»`.
Composable with basename (`image`, `about`, `vouch`, etc.) and the `:«HALLMARK»` tag for full artifact references.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_ark_yield}
Single-platform
{rbtga_ark_image}
reference.
One fact file (graft is single-platform only).

. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
graft complete with hallmark tag
.. {rbbc_show}
local image reference, registry tag, digest

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution pushes the locally-built image to
{rbtgi_repository}
tagged as `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/image:«HALLMARK»` within the hallmark subtree.
The graft operation returns `«HALLMARK»` to {rbtgo_ark_ordain}, which chains the subsequent pipeline stages automatically:
{rbtgo_ark_about} and {rbtgo_ark_vouch} in a single combined `builds.create` job (about steps followed by vouch steps) to assemble metadata and record the GRAFTED verdict.
+
*No SLSA provenance*: Grafted images have no Cloud Build provenance.
The {rbtgo_ark_vouch} pipeline records a GRAFTED verdict, explicitly marking the absence of a provenance chain.
This is a deliberate trust boundary — grafted images are accepted into the system but carry less attestation than conjured images.
+
*Push atomicity*: `docker push` is atomic per manifest — a failed push (network timeout, authentication expiry) leaves no partial state in GAR.
The director can safely retry without cleanup.
+
*Single-platform only*: Graft is specified for single-platform images only.
`docker push` of a locally-present image pushes a single manifest.
The about pipeline's platform discovery step handles this correctly, producing a single-platform `about` basename under the hallmark subtree.
Multi-platform graft is not currently specified — `buildx --load` only loads one platform into the local daemon, so true multi-platform local images would require a different push mechanism.

